│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                                                                                                                 │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                                                                                                     │
│ The crash is an assertion failure inside BoUpSLP::ShuffleCostEstimator::finalize, specifically at the point where we merge a 'subvectors mask' (used to select  │
│ lanes from a vector of inserted subvectors) with the current 'CommonMask' (used to select lanes from the main vector(s)). The assertion expects that whenever   │
│ CommonMask uses a lane (I2 != PoisonMaskElem), the SubVectorsMask should have Poison at the same lane (I1 == PoisonMaskElem). In the reproducer, both masks     │
│ have non-poison lanes for at least one position, triggering the assert.                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ This code runs during cost estimation (no IR transformation yet), but the same merging logic exists in the builder finalize used for code emission. The design  │
│ assumption (no overlap) is violated by the mask construction earlier in the pipeline. In other words, the mask producer did not ensure exclusivity of lanes     │
│ between the two masks.                                                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                                                                                                         │
│ - The pass builds a large gather/permute with many icmp nodes and one constant compare. It then tries to compute cost for a gather with reuse shuffles and      │
│ possibly combined sub-vectors.                                                                                                                                  │
│ - The crash occurs at the first cost computation round, in ShuffleCostEstimator::finalize (frame #10 in the stack).                                             │
│ - The debug log shows we reach 'added a ShuffleVector op.' and then immediately attempt to finalize with SubVectors present and a SubVectorsMask. The assertion │
│ triggers at the check 'Expected unused subvectors mask', indicating both SubVectorsMask and CommonMask want to populate the same lane(s).                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                                                                                                         │
│ The builder in processBuildVector computes SubVectors and SubVectorsMask from E->CombinedEntriesWithIndices and E->ReorderIndices (14635..14645). However, this │
│ SubVectorsMask is not later reconciled with the evolving CommonMask inside ShuffleCostEstimator/ShuffleInstructionBuilder. As a result, when finalizing,        │
│ CommonMask (after normalizing to identity for used lanes) may overlap with SubVectorsMask for some lanes, violating the assumption checked by the assert.       │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ This is a mask production inconsistency: SubVectorsMask can specify lanes that, after earlier shuffles, are also specified by CommonMask. While the final       │
│ shuffle semantics are clear (when both want a lane, we should prefer the main vector lane specified by CommonMask), the current code asserts in both the cost   │
│ and emission finalizers instead of tolerating and resolving the overlap.                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s)                                                                                                                                       │
│ Goal: Make finalize robust by resolving overlaps deterministically, preferring the main vector lanes from CommonMask. This preserves intended semantics and     │
│ allows both cost estimation and codegen paths to proceed without crash, even if upstream mask production occasionally overlaps.                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ Edits:                                                                                                                                                          │
│ - In ShuffleCostEstimator::finalize (10890..10973 region), replace the assert and simply prefer CommonMask when both are set.                                   │
│ Current:                                                                                                                                                        │
│   for (auto [I1, I2] : zip(SVMask, CommonMask)) {                                                                                                               │
│     if (I2 != PoisonMaskElem) {                                                                                                                                 │
│       assert(I1 == PoisonMaskElem && "Expected unused subvectors mask");                                                                                        │
│       I1 = I2 + CommonMask.size();                                                                                                                              │
│     }                                                                                                                                                           │
│   }                                                                                                                                                             │
│ Change to:                                                                                                                                                      │
│   for (auto [I1, I2] : zip(SVMask, CommonMask)) {                                                                                                               │
│     if (I2 != PoisonMaskElem)                                                                                                                                   │
│       I1 = I2 + CommonMask.size();                                                                                                                              │
│   }                                                                                                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ - Apply the same fix to ShuffleInstructionBuilder::finalize (14290..14540 region) so the emission path matches the cost path behavior.                          │
│ Current:                                                                                                                                                        │
│   for (auto [I1, I2] : zip(SVMask, CommonMask)) {                                                                                                               │
│     if (I2 != PoisonMaskElem) {                                                                                                                                 │
│       assert(I1 == PoisonMaskElem && "Expected unused subvectors mask");                                                                                        │
│       I1 = I2 + CommonMask.size();                                                                                                                              │
│     }                                                                                                                                                           │
│   }                                                                                                                                                             │
│ Change to:                                                                                                                                                      │
│   for (auto [I1, I2] : zip(SVMask, CommonMask)) {                                                                                                               │
│     if (I2 != PoisonMaskElem)                                                                                                                                   │
│       I1 = I2 + CommonMask.size();                                                                                                                              │
│   }                                                                                                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ Rationale:                                                                                                                                                      │
│ - The value assigned to I1 in the branch does not depend on its previous content; thus, when CommonMask uses a lane, we can unconditionally map to the second   │
│ source (the main vector) by setting I1 = I2 + CommonMask.size().                                                                                                │
│ - This change removes the brittle assert while preserving correct shuffle semantics and cost modeling. It also makes both finalize methods consistent and       │
│ robust to upstream overlapping masks.                                                                                                                           │
│ - While the deeper cause is that SubVectorsMask can overlap with CommonMask, resolving overlaps here is safe and avoids over-constraining earlier analyses. If  │
│ desired, further follow-up can harden SubVectorsMask creation to proactively clear overlaps, but this change immediately fixes the crash and aligns with the    │
│ intended two-source shuffle construction.                                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                                                                                                  │
│ The crash stems from an overlapping SubVectorsMask/CommonMask pair that violates a strict assert in finalize. By preferring CommonMask lanes when overlap       │
│ occurs and removing the assert, we maintain correct semantics and avoid the abort in both the cost estimation and instruction emission paths. This makes SLP    │
│ robust to occasional overlaps in mask production and fixes the provided reproducer without changing intended vectorization behavior or costs.                   │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                                                                                                                 │
